<paragraph id="FA58B568906FFFF2FDA2FC69FDDF40D8" blockId="5.[556,1108,659,1073]" lastBlockId="5.[140,1108,1082,1671]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">
These represent the first verifiable records of this species in North America (see below) (
<figureCitation id="62DCA9ED906FFFF2FBF9FC14FB9947D2" box="[1026,1090,976,1002]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[140,174,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[139,1108,903,1603]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[140,1108,903,1601]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Distribution of Ilyobates bennetti, Meotica exilis, Meotica “pallens,” Lathrobium fulvipenne, and Oxytelus sculptus in eastern Canada." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3773938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3773938/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The specimens collected in Point Pleasant Park were found in scolytine galleries under the bark of a dead white pine (
<taxonomicName id="3DE7CEEB906FFFF2FCDFFBFEFC68406C" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[804,947,1082,1108]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="strobus">
<emphasis id="C893697A906FFFF2FCDFFBFEFC68406C" box="[804,947,1082,1108]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Pinus strobus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., 
<taxonomicName id="3DE7CEEB906FFFF2FC1AFBFEFB93406D" authorityName="Sprengel ex F.Rudolphi" authorityYear="1830" box="[993,1096,1082,1109]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Pinaceae</taxonomicName>
). Co-inhabiting 
<taxonomicName id="3DE7CEEB906FFFF2FEC1FB99FE6C404F" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[314,439,1117,1143]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
included 
<taxonomicName id="3DE7CEEB906FFFF2FDC9FB99FC48404F" authority="(Say, 1834)" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[562,915,1117,1143]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nudobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cephalus">
<emphasis id="C893697A906FFFF2FDC9FB99FCD9404F" box="[562,770,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Nudobius cephalus</emphasis>
(Say, 1834)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="3DE7CEEB906FFFF2FC5CFB99FB9C4040" authorityName="Latreille, 1803-" authorityYear="1802" box="[935,1095,1117,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Staphylinidae</taxonomicName>
); and 
<taxonomicName id="3DE7CEEB906FFFF2FF44FB44FD8240A2" authority="(Kirby, 1837)" baseAuthorityName="Kirby" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[191,601,1152,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Polygraphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipennis">
<emphasis id="C893697A906FFFF2FF44FB44FE6F40A2" box="[191,436,1152,1178]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Polygraphus rufipennis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9E76C899906FFFF2FE3EFB44FD8A40A2" author="Kirby WF" box="[453,593,1152,1178]" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" refId="ref10004" refString="Kirby WF (1837) Th e insects. In: Richardson J (Ed) Fauna boreali-Americana or the Zoology of the northern parts of British America, containing descriptions of the objects of natural history collected on the late northern land expeditions, under the command of Captain Sir John Franklin, Fletcher, RN. Norwich, xxxix + 325 pp." type="book" year="1837">Kirby, 1837</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3DE7CEEB906FFFF2FD6DFB44FB8F40A2" authority="LeConte, 1876" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1876" box="[662,1108,1152,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Pityophthorus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cariniceps">
<emphasis id="C893697A906FFFF2FD6DFB44FC4640A2" box="[662,925,1152,1178]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="156">Pityophthorus cariniceps</emphasis>
LeConte, 1876
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="3DE7CEEB906FFFF2FF6FFB67FEE04085" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[148,315,1187,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Curculionidae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="3DE7CEEB906FFFF2FEBFFB67FE654086" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" box="[324,446,1187,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Scolytinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Scolytinae</taxonomicName>
). Th e specimen at Frenchman’s Cave was collected in a wet, mossy area in a gypsum sinkhole.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
